The paper focuses on the development of a visual analytics system for discovering biases in machine learning models, which involves the integration of techniques from human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of defining fairness in machine learning, which relates to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper presents case studies on predicting income and recidivism, which fall under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI), respectively.
